******* Copyright for the Greek Bible "Septuagint translation of the Old Testament and the Original New Testament" *******
After exhaustive search we could not identify any legal copyright holder for the Greek Bible: the Greek Old Testament is the 
Septuagint translation of the 3rd century BC and the Greek New Testament is the original form of the books that make up the
New Testament as they appeared in Koine Greek in the first and second AD century. 
The Biblical text is gained from the website http://www.bibles.gr/
